04/01/2005
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH Justice Minister Slobodan Kovac confirmed on Monday (3 January) that BiH prosecutors expect to take over several war crimes cases from the UN war crimes tribunal later this month. 
He added that BiH prosecutors also anticipate new indictments from the tribunal, but did not elaborate.
In other news, the BiH State Information and Protection Agency has assumed control over financial transactions in BiH. 
The move is aimed at boosting the fight against money laundering and the funding of terrorism. 
(Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 04/01/05; PBS BiH - 03/01/05)
